0.user_question: Will made 104 dollars mowing lawns over the summer. If he spent 41 dollars buying new mower blades, how many 9 dollar games could he buy with the money he had left?

ost_step.1: Subtract the cost of the mower blades from the amount of money Will made.

direct_answer.text: Let's think step by step. Will made 104 dollars. He spent 41 dollars on mower blades. That means he has 104 - 41 = 63 dollars left. With this 63 dollars, Will can buy 63 / 9 = 7 games because we divide the remaining money by 9 to see how many games he can buy. We round down since you cannot buy a fraction of a game. However, since the answer needs to be a whole number, and he can afford exactly one more 9 dollar game than 7 (because 63 divided by 9 equals 7), we add one to our previous answer. Therefore, 7 + 1 = 8 games. The answer is: 7.
